  "excerpt": "A Roman bakery staple: a crumbly pasta frolla tart shell filled with a thick hazelnut chocolate spread and finished with a pastry lattice. The filling is a homemade hazelnut and dark chocolate version, roasted hazelnuts blended with chocolate, cream, and a little butter. Simpler than it sounds, and the flavour is considerably better than a jar-based version.",
