  "sourceType": "PUBLIC_DOMAIN",
  "sourceNotes": "Crostata is a standard Italian open-pastry tart documented in Italian baking literature from the eighteenth century onward. Pellegrino Artusi, La Scienza in Cucina e l'Arte di Mangiar Bene (1891, freely available at Project Gutenberg IT), describes the crostata format with various fillings. Chocolate and hazelnut combinations in Italian confectionery are documented in Piedmontese and Roman food literature from the nineteenth century, with hazelnut chocolate preparations described in Italian domestic cookery guides published before 1928.",
