    {
      "slug": "hazelnut-chocolate-spread",
      "term": "Homemade hazelnut chocolate spread",
      "definition": "A smooth filling made by blending roasted hazelnuts with melted dark chocolate, cream, and a little butter. Roasting the hazelnuts is not optional: raw hazelnuts produce a starchy, bitter flavour. Rub the skins off after roasting in a clean cloth while still warm. Blend while the chocolate mixture is still warm for the smoothest result; the mixture stiffens as it cools and can be rewarmed gently if it becomes too thick to spread."
    }
  ],
